The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Second ODI highlights
                                                                                                                       7                                      Second ODI highlights
                      
	r Martin Guptill (on 11) completed 1,000 runs in one-day cricket on Wednesday. He is the fourth youngest New Zealand player to reach the landmark.         
	r Guptill registered his 8th ODI fifty and his third against India.         
	r His score of 70 was Guptils highest runs against India in ODIs. His previous best was 64 at Napier in March 2009.         
	r Daniel Vettori (on 21) became the first New Zealander and the ninth player, overall, to score 2,000 runs and take 250-plus wickets in ODIs.         
	r Deepak Patel (24), Vettori (2), John Bracewell (1) and Nathan McCullum (1) are the slow bowlers to have opened the bowling for New Zealand in ODIs.         
	r Murali Vijays 33 was his highest score in ODIs. The Indian opener is yet to score a fifty after 7 innings.         
	r Gautam Gambhir scored his 8th ODI century Wednesday, his fifth as opener, first against New Zealand and first as captain.         
	r Gambhirs last century came against Sri Lanka in Calcutta on December 24, 2009, 11 innings ago.         
	r The only other left-handed Indian captain to have scored an ODI century is Sourav Ganguly. He scored 11 hundreds.         
	r With this defeat, New Zealand have now lost eight of their nine last ODIs. One ended with no result.         
	r Wednesdays match was New Zealands first ODI at Jaipur.           MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                 
